<h4>  The core routines in this package have been developed to reduce longslit and multi-slit data from several, optical spectrometers on the Keck, Gemini, MMT, and Lick telescopes.  The routines were initially developed for observations of faint point sources (quasars) but have been tested on 
bright point sources and relatively bright galaxies.

